<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8c1da0d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s229D"><num value="229D">§ 229D.</num><heading> Injunctions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The United States may obtain in a civil action an injunction against—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c1da0e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s229D/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the conduct prohibited under section 229 or 229C of this title; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb8c1da0f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s229D/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the preparation or solicitation to engage in conduct prohibited under section 229 or 229D <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002030">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002030"><num>1</num> So in original.</note> of this title.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb8c1da10-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/105/277/dI/tII/s201/a">Pub. L. 105–277, div. I, title II, § 201(a)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-21">Oct. 21, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/2681-869">112 Stat. 2681–869</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
